ORLANDO Pirates chairman Dr Irvin Khoza has lost another wife. Pirates confirmed the passing of Khoza's wife Matina Elsie Khoza. IRVIN KHOZA'S WIFE AUSI MANTWA DIES This is Khoza's second loss following the passing of Mme Yvonne Mantwa Kgotleng-Khoza, who was laid to rest back in January. "The Khoza Family is announcing the sad passing of Mme Matina Elsie Khoza, the wife of Dr. Irvin Khoza, mother of Sonono, the late Zodwa, Nkosana and Mpumi Khoza," the club said in a statement that was released on their website."Mme Matina, who was affectionately referred to by everybody, including her ten grandchildren, as Mama, has been in and out of hospital in the last few years battling ill health.  "She sadly passed at 09h11 this morning, Thursday 23 July 2020. She was 69 years of age. "The Khoza Family pleads with the public to help us observe restrictions imposed on the nation by the Covid-19 pandemic. There will, as a result, be no visitations and prayer services held at home."